<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-9380] ColumnFamilySplit length field is not serialized</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-9380</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The CqlRecordReader uses the InputSplit.getLength() method to populate it&apos;s totalRowCount field. It uses this when calculating the progress of a job.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The length field of ColumnFamilySplit is not serialized by the write and readFields methods so the totalRowCount in CqlRecordReader is always 0.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12829834">CASSANDRA-9380</key>
            <summary>ColumnFamilySplit length field is not serialized</summary>
