                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14543622" author="jbellis" created="Thu, 14 May 2015 12:49:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Is this a new regression?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14543712" author="mike_tr_adamson" created="Thu, 14 May 2015 14:18:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Sorry I should have put it in the description. This usage of this was introduced by &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-8358&quot; title=&quot;Bundled tools shouldn&amp;#39;t be using Thrift API&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-8358&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-8358&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14543957" author="philipthompson" created="Thu, 14 May 2015 16:26:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=mikea&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;mikea&quot;&gt;mikea&lt;/a&gt;, does the attached patch fix the issue?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14543962" author="philipthompson" created="Thu, 14 May 2015 16:31:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m worried about the serialization on upgrade in a mixed version cluster. Attaching a v2 that puts the length field in a hopefully safer place.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14544048" author="mike_tr_adamson" created="Thu, 14 May 2015 17:15:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=philipthompson&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;philipthompson&quot;&gt;philipthompson&lt;/a&gt; Would it make sense to catch EOFException on the read so that it would work on a mixed version cluster?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14544204" author="philipthompson" created="Thu, 14 May 2015 19:04:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Checking for EOFException in v3&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14545229" author="mike_tr_adamson" created="Fri, 15 May 2015 09:46:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14545325" author="iamaleksey" created="Fri, 15 May 2015 11:17:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed to trunk as &lt;tt&gt;81b0acb2a9a67dd122087a00d2ec70e2b48b0a38&lt;/tt&gt;, thanks.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
